Notices about unscrupulous online stores will be distributed to Muscovites.
In Moscow, a notice is about to be released that will describe how to avoid falling victim to an online store.
Rospotrebnadzor reported this, writes M24.
It is reported that the agency's experts are preparing a notice, which will help citizens to properly choose an online store and to recognise possibly fraudulent schemes.
The intention of this brochure is to cover several sections.
These will include general information and the legal framework, the terms of delivery for goods, and ways to protect one's legal rights.
